Class DBStoredDataAccess

java.lang.Object
  testbed.db.DBStoredDataAccess

public class DBStoredDataAccess
extends java.lang.Object

This is an interface to access the data stored in the DB mostly for the GUI and to store data in the DB for the SimEng.

Author:
Guillaume Muller

verifyUser

public boolean verifyUser(java.lang.String _username,
                          java.lang.String _password)
Verifies username and password against table of existing username/password pairs. Used by GameMonitorInterface ViewPanel for verifying a user's viewing privileges.

Parameters:
_username - A String representing the username.
_password - A String representing the password.
Returns:
boolean, returns true if username exists and correct password is submitted, returns false if username doesn't exist or password is incorrect.

createUser

public boolean createUser(java.lang.String _username,
                          java.lang.String _password)
                   throws DatabaseException
Creates a new username/password pair in table of existing username/password pairs. Either creates a new user if the username is unique or accepts correct password if username already exists. Used by GameMonitorInterface JoinPanel to create new users when registering agents.

Parameters:
_username - A String representing the username.
_password - A String representing the password.
Returns:
boolean, returns false if an incorrect password is submitted with a preexisting username.
Throws:
DatabaseException
